Security Checklist

Enable encryption at rest for all storage resources (S3, EBS, RDS, ElastiCache).
Never use 0.0.0.0/0 in security group ingress without explicit justification.
Enforce MFA for all IAM users. Use IAM roles — not access keys — for services.
Enable CloudTrail, Config, and GuardDuty in every account managed by Terraform.
Mark sensitive outputs and variables with sensitive = true.
Block public access on all S3 buckets by default.
Use AWS KMS customer managed keys for state bucket and sensitive resources.
Implement least-privilege IAM policies. Never use AdministratorAccess.
Scan Terraform code in CI with tfsec and checkov on every pull request.
Review the Terraform plan carefully before every apply — especially resource replacements.


