Senior SRE Golden Rules

Never apply directly to production without a saved plan reviewed by a peer.
Never hardcode secrets — use Secrets Manager, Vault, or SOPS.
Never edit terraform.tfstate manually — use terraform state commands.
Never store state locally in production — always use a remote backend with locking.
Enable state locking — prevents concurrent runs from corrupting state.
Use reusable modules — one well-tested module is better than ten copies.
Avoid provisioners whenever possible — use cloud-init, user_data, or config management tools instead.
Prefer for_each over count — safer when elements are added or removed.
Prefer apply -replace over taint — modern and explicit.
Separate environments — use separate state files and ideally separate accounts.
Design for High Availability — multi-AZ, multi-region where RPO/RTO demands it.
Design for Disaster Recovery — state versioning, runbooks, and regular recovery drills.
Build idempotent infrastructure — every terraform apply on unchanged config should produce no changes.
Automate everything — if you do it more than once, codify it.


